Patch Set 7: Verified+1 Code-Review+1

(3 comments)

Thanks for pointing the problem tzplatform_mkpath usage. This has been fixed by an update on tizen-platform-config: see https://review.tizen.org/gerrit/#/c/16693/

The pointers returned by tzplatform_get() and other helper functions are now allocated once for a given result (in separate buffers). This way, we'll avoid possible mistakes due to semantics.

For the debate on whether to change macros to macros with arguments, I let you decide which is the best. For internal use of a macro inside a package, this is a good idea. But if the macro is in a public header, I'd recommend to let the macro name as is. Otherwise, this may impact all other packages using the public header.
